{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3551640,"name":"Mitchell","username":"redbarron345","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ebca7d/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-09T02:39:11.730Z","cooked":"<p>Hello there, I am a mentor for team 9626, and we are trying to get the code finished for our 2 stage elevator. We were able to get the elevator to position (within 0.01") but the elevator couldn’t hold itself up so we started to increase kG to account for the weight due to gravity. When doing this, we now have an issue of the elevator jumping up 6 inches when enabling the robot, and when getting close to a position holds itself up but oscillates like crazy around that point. Is this just a tuning issue or am I missing something else? Any input is appreciated.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">package frc.robot.subsystems;

import com.revrobotics.spark.SparkLowLevel.MotorType;

import com.revrobotics.spark.SparkMax;

import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.ElevatorFeedforward;
